---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/landing/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/landing/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Experimental Linux builds for shuru"
  description="Shuru now publishes experimental Linux ARM64 builds with the KVM backend. Setup details live on the Linux page."
>
  <div class="dot-grid min-h-screen">
    <Nav />

    <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
      <article class="relative border-x border-border pt-36 pb-0 md:pt-48">
        <span class="section-label article-label">Blog</span>

        <div class="px-8 pt-8 pb-6 md:px-16 md:pt-12 md:pb-8">
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-dim">April 15, 2026</div>
          <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
            Shuru on Linux
            <br />
            <span class="text-muted">is live for ARM64 hosts.</span>
          </h1>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-section border-t border-dashed border-border px-8 pt-8 pb-4 md:px-16 md:pt-12 md:pb-6">
          <p>
            Shuru now publishes Linux CLI builds in GitHub Releases. They target Linux ARM64 and use a KVM backend
            in place of Apple's Virtualization.framework. Homebrew remains macOS-only; on Linux, the install
            script is the path.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is the experimental track. It is useful for evaluating shuru on ARM servers and Linux workstations,
            but it is not production-ready yet while we keep closing gaps between the macOS and Linux backends.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-section border-t border-dashed border-border px-8 pt-8 pb-4 md:px-16 md:pt-12 md:pb-6">
          <h2>Setup and prerequisites</h2>
          <p>
            Full instructions live on the Linux setup page: prerequisites (ARM64, <code>/dev/kvm</code>,
            <code>kvm</code> group), install script, first run, and troubleshooting.
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="/linux" class="text-amber hover:underline">Read the Linux setup guide &rarr;</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-dashed border-border px-8 py-8 md:px-16 md:py-10">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-3 font-mono text-sm">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/superhq-ai/shuru/releases"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-muted transition-colors hover:text-amber"
            >
              GitHub Releases &rarr;
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/superhq-ai/shuru"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-muted transition-colors hover:text-amber"
            >
              GitHub repository &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-6 md:px-16">
          <span class="measure">article</span>
          <div class="h-px flex-1 border-t border-dashed border-dim"></div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>

    <Footer />

    <div class="h-12"></div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-label {
    top: calc(9rem - 8px);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .article-label {
      top: calc(12rem - 8px);
    }
  }

  .prose-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .prose-section p + p {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-section code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
